{"isSidechain":true,"agentId":"1f8cbc3b-2744-4bd","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Investigate the cluster advisor workflow test patterns and how the workflow handles variant signals. I need to understand:\n\n1. Read `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/workflow/analysis_workflow.go` — focus on how variant signals are processed in the main loop, especially the `receivedSignal` handling and how `reconcileResult.Done` is determined.\n\n2. Read `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/executor/handler_test.go` — understand the test patterns for failVariant and HandleVariant.\n\n3. Read `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/executor/handler_component_test.go` — understand component test patterns.\n\n4. Check if the workflow has any existing tests: search for files matching `*workflow*test*` or `*analysis_workflow*test*` in the clusteradvisor directory.\n\n5. Check what `VariantCompletedSignal` looks like in the workflow vs the executor types. Read `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/executor/types/types.go`.\n\n6. Read the `AnalysisVariantRequest` in mq/types.go to check if trigger type is included. If not, check whether the analysis record is accessible from the workflow (it knows the analysis ID).\n\nReport back the key findings: how signals work, what test infrastructure exists, and whether the workflow can determine if a failed variant was the baseline."},"timestamp":"2026-06-08T11:16:01.651Z","cwd":"/Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast"}
